AGI -&nbsp;Volodymyr Zelensky and Donald Trump met openly at the White House, during the meeting for the signing of an agreement on the sharing of the mineral wealth of Ukraine and to discuss a peace agreement with Russia. "You are not showing gratitude at all. It's not a good thing," the president of the United States said. "It will be very difficult to do business like this," he added.
Earlier Trump said he was "close enough" to reach an agreement to end the war in Ukraine. "This is an exciting moment, but the really exciting moment will be when the weapons will shut up and we will find a deal. And I think we're very close," Trump told reporters at Oval Studio.
Trump said he considered himself a "arbiter" and a "mediator" between Russia and Ukraine to reach peace. "I am here as an arbitrator, as a mediator, to some extent, between two parts that have been very hostile," he said in some statements to journalists from the Oval Studio of the White House.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky: "Putin is a killer, we will not only accept the ceasefire"</h2>
Zelensy called Vladimir Putin a killer. "He's a killer - he said - I don't want compromises." The Ukrainian leader said not to trust the Russian president and for this reason he will not only settle for the ceasefire. "From 2015 - said Zelensky to the White House - Putin broke 25 times, for 25 times he did not respect his signature, for 25 times he violated the ceasefire. That is why we will not only accept the ceasefire and we will not go ahead without security."
<h2>Trump gela Zelensky, "or make the deal or we are out"</h2>
" Either you make a deal or we get out, and if we go out, you'll have to see it yourself. I don't think it's gonna be a good thing," Trump turned to Zelensky. "And - he added - you will have to face it even if you do not have the right cards. But once we sign that deal, you'll be in a much better position. But you are not showing any gratitude and this is not beautiful." "I'll be honest - he continued - it's not a good thing."
<h2>Vance to Zelensky, lacks of respect to Americans
Vice President JD Vance, present at the Oval Studio, accused Zelensky of "deserving respect" to the Americans. "We do not come to the White House to lack respect to the President before the Americans." In an unexpectedly hard confrontation, Donald Trump stated that it would be "very difficult" to negotiate with Volodymyr Zelensky, responded with anger that he should have been "free", after stating that the Ukrainian president had put himself "in a very bad position" and had not "cards in hand". &nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky, first step agreement for security guarantees
Zelensky said that the economic agreement with the United States is a first step towards obtaining "genuine security guarantees" for his country. "I hope this document, this first document, is the first step towards real security security for Ukraine. And, of course, we ask the United States to continue to provide support. It's very important to us," he told his American counterpart.
<h2>Trump, the mineral agreement is very fair
Trump told his Ukrainian counterpart that the agreement that allows the exploitation of the natural resources of Ukraine by the United States would be "very fair". The agreement will give the United States access to essential minerals as part of a general plan to help Ukraine recover after a truce in the war with Russia.
<h2>Trump shows Zelensky and jokes, today is elegant dress</h2>
From a new video, which the Guardian publishes "by courtesy of Trump's assistant and advisor for communication, Margo Martin" we understand Donald Trump's joke at Volodymyr Zelensky on arrival at the White House. Indicating the black uniform worn by Ukrainian president, Trump jokes: "Oh, look, you're all dressed up. Today - shouts to journalists - it's all dressed up elegant!"
